<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-222-252 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 390 999</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 12 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple announces 7.0 tools. (MacApp 3.0, ToolServer, SourceBug andBalloonWriter) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   System 7.0 (Operating system) (Product enhancement)MacApp 3.0 (Program development software) (Product introduction)Toolserver (Program development software) (Product introduction)BalloonWriter (Program development software) (Productintroduction)Sourcebug (Program development software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware packagesProgram Development ToolsDebugging Tools.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>APPLE ANNOUNCES 7.0 TOOLS 02/12/91 CUPERTINO, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1991 FEB 12(NB) --  Apple Computer has announced four development tools, MacApp 3.0,ToolServer, SourceBug and BalloonWriter, for its as yet unreleased MacintoshSystem 7.0 operating system.andP;  The products were announced during the secondannual MacApp Developers Association (MADA) conference held in Phoenix,Arizona.andM;MacApp 3.0 is the latest version of Apple's object-oriented framework forapplications.andP;  It provides developers the objects such as scroll bars,multiple windows, printing, cut and paste, undo and menus needed to programstandard elements of Macintosh applications..andM;ToolServer is a stand-alone, tool-execution environment for MacintoshProgrammer Workshop (MPW) tools.andP;  Apple states that programmers will be ableto take advantage of ToolServer by running development processes--such ascompiling and linking--on their computer in the background, or on a remoteMacintosh personal computer when connected to an AppleTalk network.andP;  Appleevent messages, a System 7.0 feature, will allow programmers to control theseprocesses between ToolServer and their development systemandM;SourceBug is a direct-manipulation, source level debugger that runs on SystemSoftware 6.x, 7.0 and A/UX, Apple's version of the industry-standard ATandamp;TUNIX operating system.andP;  In addition to supporting the debugging ofconventional, procedural programs, SourceBug will provide features for thedebugging of object-oriented programs, such as those developed in MacApp.andM;BalloonWriter is a tool for creating Balloon Help for application programsrunning on Macintosh personal computers using System 7.0.andP;  Balloon Help is afeature built into System 7.0 intended to allow programmers to provide anintuitive on-line help system applications menus, windows and dialog boxes.andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19910211/Press Contact: JackiePromes, Apple Computer Inc., 408-974-3609)</TEXT></DOC>